The article discusses the 20th anniversary of the State Department designating Lebanese Hizballah as a foreign terrorist organization. Thomas Bossert, Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism, calls for a global response to combat the group in an op-ed in Le Monde. The Trump Administration aims to support legitimate state institutions in Lebanon and expose Hizballah's nefarious behavior. The United States recently arrested two U.S. citizens for allegedly acting on behalf of Hizballah's international terrorism unit. The U.S. government is offering rewards for information leading to the capture of Hizballah leaders involved in terrorist activities. An interactive graphic provides an overview of Hizballah's operational activity since its inception.